{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"I want to talk about the election."},{"time":3000,"text":"For the first time in the United States, a predominantly white group of voters"},{"time":6000,"text":"voted for an African-American candidate for President."},{"time":9000,"text":"And in fact Barack Obama did quite well."},{"time":11000,"text":"He won 375 electoral votes."},{"time":13000,"text":"And he won about 70 million popular votes"},{"time":16000,"text":"more than any other presidential candidate --"},{"time":18000,"text":"of any race, of any party -- in history."},{"time":21000,"text":"If you compare how Obama did against how John Kerry had done four years earlier --"},{"time":25000,"text":"Democrats really like seeing this transition here,"},{"time":28000,"text":"where almost every state becomes bluer, becomes more democratic --"},{"time":32000,"text":"even states Obama lost, like out west,"},{"time":34000,"text":"those states became more blue."},{"time":36000,"text":"In the south, in the northeast, almost everywhere"},{"time":39000,"text":"but with a couple of exceptions here and there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":42000,"text":"One exception is in Massachusetts."},{"time":44000,"text":"That was John Kerry's home state."},{"time":46000,"text":"No big surprise, Obama couldn't do better than Kerry there."},{"time":48000,"text":"Or in Arizona, which is John McCain's home,"},{"time":50000,"text":"Obama didn't have much improvement."},{"time":52000,"text":"But there is also this part of the country, kind of in the middle region here."},{"time":54000,"text":"This kind of Arkansas, Tennessee, Oklahoma, West Virginia region."},{"time":58000,"text":"Now if you look at '96, Bill Clinton --"},{"time":60000,"text":"the last Democrat to actually win -- how he did in '96,"},{"time":63000,"text":"you see real big differences in this part of the country right here,"},{"time":66000,"text":"the kind of Appalachians, Ozarks, highlands region, as I call it:"},{"time":70000,"text":"20 or 30 point swings"},{"time":72000,"text":"from how Bill Clinton did in '96 to how Obama did"},{"time":74000,"text":"in 2008."},{"time":76000,"text":"Yes Bill Clinton was from Arkansas, but these are very, very profound differences."}]},{"cues":[{"time":81000,"text":"So, when we think about parts of the country like Arkansas, you know."},{"time":83000,"text":"There is a book written called, \"What's the Matter with Kansas?\""},{"time":86000,"text":"But really the question here -- Obama did relatively well in Kansas."},{"time":89000,"text":"He lost badly but every Democrat does."},{"time":91000,"text":"He lost no worse than most people do."},{"time":93000,"text":"But yeah, what's the matter with Arkansas?"},{"time":97000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":98000,"text":"And when we think of Arkansas we tend to have pretty negative connotations."},{"time":101000,"text":"We think of a bunch of rednecks, quote, unquote, with guns."},{"time":104000,"text":"And we think people like this probably don't want to vote"},{"time":107000,"text":"for people who look like this and are named Barack Obama."},{"time":110000,"text":"We think it's a matter of race. And is this fair?"},{"time":113000,"text":"Are we kind of stigmatizing people from Arkansas, and this part of the country?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":116000,"text":"And the answer is: it is at least partially fair."},{"time":119000,"text":"We know that race was a factor, and the reason why we know that"},{"time":121000,"text":"is because we asked those people."},{"time":123000,"text":"Actually we didn't ask them, but when they conducted"},{"time":125000,"text":"exit polls in every state,"},{"time":127000,"text":"in 37 states, out of the 50,"},{"time":129000,"text":"they asked a question, that was pretty direct, about race."},{"time":132000,"text":"They asked this question."},{"time":134000,"text":"In deciding your vote for President today, was the race"},{"time":136000,"text":"of the candidate a factor?"},{"time":138000,"text":"We're looking for people that said, \"Yes, race was a factor;"},{"time":141000,"text":"moreover it was an important factor, in my decision,\""},{"time":143000,"text":"and people who voted for John McCain"},{"time":146000,"text":"as a result of that factor,"},{"time":148000,"text":"maybe in combination with other factors, and maybe alone."},{"time":150000,"text":"We're looking for this behavior among white voters"},{"time":153000,"text":"or, really, non-black voters."}]},{"cues":[{"time":156000,"text":"So you see big differences in different parts"},{"time":158000,"text":"of the country on this question."},{"time":160000,"text":"In Louisiana, about one in five white voters"},{"time":163000,"text":"said, \"Yes, one of the big reasons why I voted against Barack Obama"},{"time":166000,"text":"is because he was an African-American.\""},{"time":168000,"text":"If those people had voted for Obama,"},{"time":170000,"text":"even half of them, Obama would have won Louisiana safely."},{"time":174000,"text":"Same is true with, I think, all of these states you see on the top of the list."},{"time":176000,"text":"Meanwhile, California, New York, we can say, \"Oh we're enlightened\""},{"time":180000,"text":"but you know, certainly a much lower incidence of this"},{"time":182000,"text":"admitted, I suppose,"},{"time":184000,"text":"manifestation of racially-based voting."},{"time":187000,"text":"Here is the same data on a map."},{"time":189000,"text":"You kind of see the relationship between"},{"time":191000,"text":"the redder states of where more people responded and said,"},{"time":193000,"text":"\"Yes, Barack Obama's race was a problem for me.\""},{"time":196000,"text":"You see, comparing the map to '96, you see an overlap here."},{"time":199000,"text":"This really seems to explain"},{"time":201000,"text":"why Barack Obama did worse"},{"time":203000,"text":"in this one part of the country."}]},{"cues":[{"time":205000,"text":"So we have to ask why."},{"time":207000,"text":"Is racism predictable in some way?"},{"time":209000,"text":"Is there something driving this?"},{"time":211000,"text":"Is it just about some weird stuff that goes on in Arkansas"},{"time":213000,"text":"that we don't understand, and Kentucky?"},{"time":215000,"text":"Or are there more systematic factors at work?"},{"time":217000,"text":"And so we can look at a bunch of different variables."},{"time":219000,"text":"These are things that economists and political scientists look at all the time --"},{"time":222000,"text":"things like income, and religion, education."},{"time":225000,"text":"Which of these seem to drive"},{"time":227000,"text":"this manifestation of racism"},{"time":229000,"text":"in this big national experiment we had on November 4th?"},{"time":232000,"text":"And there are a couple of these that have"},{"time":234000,"text":"strong predictive relationships,"},{"time":236000,"text":"one of which is education,"},{"time":239000,"text":"where you see the states with the fewest years of schooling"},{"time":241000,"text":"per adult are in red,"},{"time":243000,"text":"and you see this part of the country, the kind of Appalachians region,"},{"time":246000,"text":"is less educated. It's just a fact."},{"time":248000,"text":"And you see the relationship there"},{"time":250000,"text":"with the racially-based voting patterns."},{"time":253000,"text":"The other variable that's important is"},{"time":255000,"text":"the type of neighborhood that you live in."},{"time":258000,"text":"States that are more rural --"},{"time":260000,"text":"even to some extent of the states like New Hampshire and Maine --"},{"time":262000,"text":"they exhibit a little bit of"},{"time":264000,"text":"this racially-based voting against Barack Obama."},{"time":267000,"text":"So it's the combination of these two things: it's education"},{"time":269000,"text":"and the type of neighbors that you have,"},{"time":271000,"text":"which we'll talk about more in a moment."},{"time":273000,"text":"And the thing about states like Arkansas and Tennessee"},{"time":275000,"text":"is that they're both very rural,"},{"time":277000,"text":"and they are educationally impoverished."}]},{"cues":[{"time":281000,"text":"So yes, racism is predictable."},{"time":283000,"text":"These things, among maybe other variables,"},{"time":285000,"text":"but these things seem to predict it."},{"time":287000,"text":"We're going to drill down a little bit more now,"},{"time":289000,"text":"into something called the General Social Survey."},{"time":291000,"text":"This is conducted by the University of Chicago"},{"time":293000,"text":"every other year."},{"time":295000,"text":"And they ask a series of really interesting questions."},{"time":297000,"text":"In 2000 they had particularly interesting questions"},{"time":299000,"text":"about racial attitudes."},{"time":301000,"text":"One simple question they asked is,"},{"time":303000,"text":"\"Does anyone of the opposite race live in your neighborhood?\""},{"time":307000,"text":"We can see in different types of communities that the results are quite different."},{"time":310000,"text":"In cites, about 80 percent of people"},{"time":313000,"text":"have someone whom they consider a neighbor of another race,"},{"time":316000,"text":"but in rural communities, only about 30 percent."},{"time":319000,"text":"Probably because if you live on a farm, you might not have a lot of neighbors, period."},{"time":322000,"text":"But nevertheless, you're not having a lot of interaction with people"},{"time":325000,"text":"who are unlike you."},{"time":327000,"text":"So what we're going to do now is take the white people in the survey"},{"time":330000,"text":"and split them between those who have black neighbors --"},{"time":333000,"text":"or, really, some neighbor of another race --"},{"time":335000,"text":"and people who have only white neighbors."},{"time":338000,"text":"And we see in some variables"},{"time":340000,"text":"in terms of political attitudes, not a lot of difference."},{"time":342000,"text":"This was eight years ago, some people were more Republican back then."},{"time":345000,"text":"But you see Democrats versus Republican,"},{"time":347000,"text":"not a big difference based on who your neighbors are."}]},{"cues":[{"time":350000,"text":"And even some questions about race -- for example"},{"time":352000,"text":"affirmative action, which is kind of a political question,"},{"time":354000,"text":"a policy question about race, if you will --"},{"time":356000,"text":"not much difference here."},{"time":358000,"text":"Affirmative action is not very popular frankly, with white voters, period."},{"time":361000,"text":"But people with black neighbors and people with mono-racial neighborhoods"},{"time":364000,"text":"feel no differently about it really."},{"time":367000,"text":"But if you probe a bit deeper and get a bit more personal if you will,"},{"time":371000,"text":"\"Do you favor a law banning interracial marriage?\""},{"time":373000,"text":"There is a big difference."},{"time":375000,"text":"People who don't have neighbors of a different race"},{"time":377000,"text":"are about twice as likely"},{"time":379000,"text":"to oppose interracial marriage as people who do."},{"time":382000,"text":"Just based on who lives in your immediate neighborhood around you."},{"time":385000,"text":"And likewise they asked, not in 2000, but in the same survey in 1996,"},{"time":389000,"text":"\"Would you not vote for a qualified black president?\""},{"time":393000,"text":"You see people without neighbors who are African-American who"},{"time":395000,"text":"were much more likely to say, \"That would give me a problem.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":398000,"text":"So it's really not even about urban versus rural."},{"time":400000,"text":"It's about who you live with."},{"time":402000,"text":"Racism is predictable. And it's predicted by"},{"time":404000,"text":"interaction or lack thereof with people unlike you, people of other races."},{"time":408000,"text":"So if you want to address it,"},{"time":410000,"text":"the goal is to facilitate interaction with people of other races."},{"time":413000,"text":"I have a couple of very obvious, I suppose,"},{"time":415000,"text":"ideas for maybe how to do that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":418000,"text":"I'm a big fan of cities."},{"time":420000,"text":"Especially if we have cites that are diverse and sustainable,"},{"time":423000,"text":"and can support people of different ethnicities and different income groups."},{"time":426000,"text":"I think cities facilitate more of the kind of networking,"},{"time":429000,"text":"the kind of casual interaction than you might have on a daily basis."},{"time":432000,"text":"But also not everyone wants to live in a city, certainly not a city like New York."},{"time":435000,"text":"So we can think more about things like street grids."},{"time":438000,"text":"This is the neighborhood where I grew up in East Lansing, Michigan."},{"time":440000,"text":"It's a traditional Midwestern community, which means you have real grid."},{"time":443000,"text":"You have real neighborhoods and real trees, and real streets you can walk on."},{"time":446000,"text":"And you interact a lot with your neighbors --"},{"time":449000,"text":"people you like, people you might not know."},{"time":451000,"text":"And as a result it's a very tolerant community,"},{"time":454000,"text":"which is different, I think, than something like this,"},{"time":456000,"text":"which is in Schaumburg, Illinois,"},{"time":458000,"text":"where every little set of houses has their own cul-de-sac"},{"time":461000,"text":"and drive-through Starbucks and stuff like that."},{"time":463000,"text":"I think that actually this type of urban design,"},{"time":466000,"text":"which became more prevalent in the 1970s and 1980s --"},{"time":469000,"text":"I think there is a relationship between that and the country becoming"},{"time":472000,"text":"more conservative under Ronald Reagan."}]},{"cues":[{"time":474000,"text":"But also here is another idea we have --"},{"time":477000,"text":"is an intercollegiate exchange program"},{"time":479000,"text":"where you have students going from New York abroad."},{"time":482000,"text":"But frankly there are enough differences within the country now"},{"time":484000,"text":"where maybe you can take a bunch of kids from NYU,"},{"time":487000,"text":"have them go study for a semester at the University of Arkansas,"},{"time":489000,"text":"and vice versa. Do it at the high school level."},{"time":492000,"text":"Literally there are people who might be in school in Arkansas or Tennessee"},{"time":495000,"text":"and might never interact in a positive affirmative way"},{"time":498000,"text":"with someone from another part of the country, or of another racial group."},{"time":502000,"text":"I think part of the education variable we talked about before"},{"time":505000,"text":"is the networking experience you get when you go to college"},{"time":507000,"text":"where you do get a mix of people that you might not interact with otherwise."}]},{"cues":[{"time":511000,"text":"But the point is, this is all good news,"},{"time":513000,"text":"because when something is predictable,"},{"time":516000,"text":"it is what I call designable."},{"time":518000,"text":"You can start thinking about solutions to solving that problem,"},{"time":520000,"text":"even if the problem is pernicious and as intractable as racism."},{"time":523000,"text":"If we understand the root causes of the behavior"},{"time":525000,"text":"and where it manifests itself and where it doesn't,"},{"time":527000,"text":"we can start to design solutions to it."},{"time":530000,"text":"So that's all I have to say. Thank you very much."},{"time":532000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}